@guozhangwang @ijuma Updated.

Thinking about this twice, even if this change does improve test runtime, it might not fix the actual issue, because hitting the timeout is independent of an additional evaluation of the test condition after the `while` loop. Actually, it might make the stability even worse, as testing the condition again, would actually be "one more try" to receive the data we are waiting for.

Therefore, I also did increase the timeout from default 30 to 60 seconds.

